-- DIARY: G7, IMF and World Bank meetings in Washington
-- 
-- Sat Oct 11, 2008 10:12pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/12/us-imf-diary-idUSTRE49B08220081012

 

 Finance ministers and central bankers from around the globe are descending on Washington for the annual meetings of the International Monetary Fund and World Bank on October 11-13. In addition, finance officials from the Group of Seven met on October 10. 

 Following is a schedule of the week's top events. All times listed are in Washington local time/GMT. Sunday, October 12 0845/1245 - Bank of Mexico Governor Guillermo Ortiz, Central Bank of Indonesia Governor Boediono and Dallas Federal Reserve Bank President Richard Fisher participate in discussion on the financial crisis at the IIF meeting. 0900/1300 - IMF and World Bank's Development Committee meets. 1100/1500 - Bank of Italy Governor Mario Draghi, chairman of the Financial Stability Forum, speaks at the IIF meeting. 1100/1500 - ECB Governor Council member Christian Noyer, Swiss National Bank Vice Chairman Philipp Hildebrand and Bank of Spain Deputy Governor Jose Vinals participate in discussion on financial stability. 1130/1530 - IIF Board holds news conference. 1130/1530 - U.K. Financial Services Authority Chairman Lord Adair Turner speaks at the IIF meeting. 1300/1700 - Russian Finance Minister Alexei Kudrin speaks at IIF meeting. 1530/1930 - Development Committee Chairman Agustin Carstens, World Bank President Robert Zoellick and IMF Managing Director Dominique Strauss-Kahn holds news conference. 1615/2015 - IMF seminar, "Turmoil in Global Financial and Commodities Markets -- Prospects and Policies" with IMF First Deputy Managing Director John Lipsky; former Federal Reserve vice chairman Roger Ferguson and George Soros. 1815/2215 - George Soros holds news conference on financial crisis Monday, October 13 Morning - U.S. Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson meets with African finance ministers. 0800/1200 - U.S. Treasury Interim Assistant Secretary for Financial Stability Neel Kashkari speaks on financial markets before the Institute of International Bankers. 0930/1330 - IMF and World Bank annual meetings opening plenary session. 1200/1600 - U.S. Treasury Deputy Secretary Robert Kimmitt and OECD Secretary General Angel Gurria participate in a briefing on Sovereign Wealth Funds. 1430/1830 - IMF and World Bank annual meetings closing session. For related diaries, please see: DIARY - U.S. Federal Reserve DIARY - European Central Bank DIARY - Polling Unit Diary for 2006 DIARY - Today in Washington DIARY - Key World Financial Events DIARY - Political and General news DIARY - Index of all Diaries DIARY - G7 Real-Time economic data DIARY - OECD countries upcoming economic data & forecast DIARY - Major Central Bank Events for 2006 NOTE: The inclusion of diary items does not necessarily mean that Reuters will file a story based on the event. IMF Spring meeting schedule available  here